title: American Gangster
awards: Nominated for 2 Oscars. Another 12 wins & 31 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: American Gangster is a gritty and entertaining throwback to classic gangster films, with its lead performers firing on all cylinders.
name: American_Gangster

title: American Pie
tomatoConsensus: So embarrassing it's believable, American Pie succeeds in bringing back the teen movie genre.
name: American_Pie

title: Anna Karenina
tomatoConsensus: Joe Wright's energetic adaptation of Tolstoy's classic romance is a bold, visually stylized work -- for both better and worse.
name: Anna_Karenina

title: A Fish Called Wanda
tomatoConsensus: Smartly written, smoothly directed, and solidly cast, A Fish Called Wanda offers a classic example of a brainy comedy with widespread appeal.
name: A_Fish_Called_Wanda

title: A Million Ways to Die in the West
tomatoConsensus: While it offers a few laughs and boasts a talented cast, Seth MacFarlane's overlong, aimless A Million Ways to Die in the West is a disappointingly scattershot affair.
name: A_Million_Ways_to_Die_in_the_West

title: A Single Man
awards: Nominated for 1 Oscar. Another 39 wins & 39 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Though the costumes are beautiful and the art direction impeccable, what stands out most from this debut by fashion designer Tom Ford is the leading performance by Colin Firth.
name: A_Single_Man

title: Big Hero 6
tomatoConsensus: Agreeably entertaining and brilliantly animated, Big Hero 6 is briskly-paced, action-packed, and often touching.
name: Big_Hero_6

title: Black Swan
tomatoConsensus: Bracingly intense, passionate, and wildly melodramatic, Black Swan glides on Darren Aronofsky's bold direction -- and a bravura performance from Natalie Portman.
name: Black_Swan

title: Boogie Nights
awards: Nominated for 3 Oscars. Another 36 wins & 38 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Grounded in strong characters, bold themes, and subtle storytelling, Boogie Nights is a groundbreaking film both for director P.T. Anderson and star Mark Wahlberg.
name: Boogie_Nights

title: Bronson
tomatoConsensus: Undeniably gripping, Bronson forces the viewer to make some hard decisions about where the line between art and exploitation lies.
name: Bronson

title: Brother Bear
awards: Nominated for 1 Oscar. Another 2 wins & 19 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Brother Bear is gentle and pleasant if unremarkable Disney fare, with so-so animation and generic plotting.
name: Brother_Bear

title: Casino Royale
awards: Won 1 BAFTA Film Award. Another 20 wins & 33 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Casino Royale disposes of the silliness and gadgetry that plagued recent James Bond outings, and Daniel Craig delivers what fans and critics have been waiting for: a caustic, haunted, intense reinvention of 007.
name: Casino_Royale

title: Chef
tomatoConsensus: Chef's charming cast and sharp, funny script add enough spice to make this feel-good comedy a flavorful -- if familiar -- treat.
name: Chef

title: Donnie Darko
tomatoConsensus: Richard Kelly's debut feature Donnie Darko is a daring, original vision, packed with jarring ideas and intelligence and featuring a remarkable performance from Jake Gyllenhaal as the troubled title character.
name: Donnie_Darko

title: Drive
awards: Nominated for 1 Oscar. Another 78 wins & 124 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: With its hyper-stylized blend of violence, music, and striking imagery, Drive represents a fully realized vision of arthouse action.
name: Drive

title: Elsa & Fred
tomatoConsensus: Boosted by charming performances by the octogenarian leads, Elsa and Fred overcomes its schmaltzy premise to make for a satisfying romantic tale.
name: Elsa___Fred

title: Full Metal Jacket
awards: Nominated for 1 Oscar. Another 9 wins & 7 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Intense, tightly constructed, and darkly comic at times, Stanley Kubrick's Full Metal Jacket may not boast the most original of themes, but it is exceedingly effective at communicating them.
name: Full_Metal_Jacket

title: Grand Piano
tomatoConsensus: Grand Piano is so tense in its best moments -- and appealingly strange overall -- that it remains rewarding in spite of its flaws.
name: Grand_Piano

title: Hook
awards: Nominated for 5 Oscars. Another 5 wins & 12 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: The look of Hook is lively indeed but Steven Spielberg directs on autopilot here, giving in too quickly to his sentimental, syrupy qualities.
name: Hook

title: Hotel Transylvania
awards: Nominated for 1 Golden Globe. Another 3 wins & 14 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Hotel Transylvania's buoyant, giddy tone may please children, but it might be a little too loud and thinly-scripted for older audiences.
name: Hotel_Transylvania

title: Inherent Vice
awards: Nominated for 2 Oscars. Another 27 wins & 59 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Inherent Vice may prove frustrating for viewers who demand absolute coherence, but it does justice to its acclaimed source material -- and should satisfy fans of director P.T. Anderson.
name: Inherent_Vice

title: Interstellar
tomatoConsensus: Interstellar represents more of the thrilling, thought-provoking, and visually resplendent filmmaking moviegoers have come to expect from writer-director Christopher Nolan, even if its intellectual reach somewhat exceeds its grasp.
name: Interstellar

title: Into the Wild
awards: Nominated for 2 Oscars. Another 26 wins & 84 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: With his sturdy cast and confident direction, Sean Penn has turned a complex work of non-fiction like Into the Wild into an accessible and poignant character study.
name: Into_the_Wild

title: Into the Woods
awards: Nominated for 3 Oscars. Another 9 wins & 52 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: On the whole, this Disney adaptation of the Sondheim classic sits comfortably at the corner of Hollywood and Broadway -- even if it darkens to its detriment in the final act.
name: Into_the_Woods

title: Invincible
tomatoConsensus: As simple and authentic as the gritty South Philly invirons in which it's set in, Invincible sends a uplifting and heartfelt message packed with an athletic enthusiasm that shouldn't be missed.
name: Invincible

title: Jack Reacher
tomatoConsensus: Jack Reacher is an above-average crime thriller with a smoothly charismatic performance from Tom Cruise.
name: Jack_Reacher

title: Jerry Maguire
tomatoConsensus: Anchored by dazzling performances from Tom Cruise, Cuba Gooding Jr., and Renee Zellweger, as well as Cameron Crowe's tender direction, Jerry Maguire meshes romance and sports with panache.
name: Jerry_Maguire

title: John Wick
tomatoConsensus: Stylish, thrilling, and giddily kinetic, John Wick serves as a satisfying return to action for Keanu Reeves -- and what looks like it could be the first of a franchise.
name: John_Wick

title: Let's Be Cops
tomatoConsensus: Damon Wayans, Jr. and Jake Johnson have comedic chemistry; unfortunately, Let's Be Cops fails to do anything with it.
name: Let's_Be_Cops

title: Looney Tunes: Back in Action
tomatoConsensus: The plot is a nonsensical, hyperactive jumble and the gags are relatively uninspired compared to the classic Looney Tunes cartoons.
name: Looney_Tunes__Back_in_Action

title: Mean Girls
tomatoConsensus: Funnier and more smartly written than the average teen comedy.
name: Mean_Girls

title: Monsters University
awards: Nominated for 1 BAFTA Film Award. Another 13 wins & 46 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: It doesn't scale the heights of Pixar's finest efforts, but Monsters University is still funny and thoughtful family entertainment for viewers of any age.
name: Monsters_University

title: Moulin Rouge!
tomatoConsensus: A love-it-or-hate-it experience, Moulin Rouge is all style, all giddy, over-the-top spectacle. But it's also daring in its vision and wildly original.
name: Moulin_Rouge!

title: Mulan
awards: Nominated for 1 Oscar. Another 17 wins & 20 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Exploring themes of family duty and honor, Mulan breaks new ground as a Disney film, while still bringing vibrant animation and sprightly characters to the screen.
name: Mulan

title: My Week with Marilyn
awards: Nominated for 2 Oscars. Another 22 wins & 53 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Michelle Williams shines in My Week with Marilyn, capturing the magnetism and vulnerability of Marilyn Monroe.
name: My_Week_with_Marilyn

title: Nightcrawler
awards: Nominated for 1 Oscar. Another 46 wins & 75 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Restless, visually sleek, and powered by a lithe star performance from Jake Gyllenhaal, Nightcrawler offers dark, thought-provoking thrills.
name: Nightcrawler

title: Night at the Museum: Secret of the Tomb
tomatoConsensus: While not without its moments, Night at the Museum: Secret of the Tomb is a less-than-inspired sendoff for the trilogy.
name: Night_at_the_Museum__Secret_of_the_Tomb

title: Predestination
tomatoConsensus: Fun genre fare with uncommon intelligence, Predestination serves as a better-than-average sci-fi adventure -- and offers a starmaking turn from Sarah Snook.
name: Predestination

title: Pulp Fiction
tomatoConsensus: One of the most influential films of the 1990s, Pulp Fiction is a delirious post-modern mix of neo-noir thrills, pitch-black humor, and pop-culture touchstones.
name: Pulp_Fiction

title: RED
awards: Nominated for 1 Golden Globe. Another 2 wins & 16 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: It may not be the killer thrill ride you'd expect from an action movie with a cast of this caliber, but Red still thoroughly outshines most of its big-budget counterparts with its wit and style.
name: RED

title: Robin Hood
tomatoConsensus: Ridley Scott's revisionist take on this oft-told tale offers some fine acting and a few gripping action sequences, but it's missing the thrill of adventure that made Robin Hood a legend in the first place.
name: Robin_Hood

title: Seventh Son
tomatoConsensus: Seventh Son squanders an excellent cast and some strange storyline ingredients, leaving audiences with one disappointingly dull fantasy adventure.
name: Seventh_Son

title: Shakespeare in Love
tomatoConsensus: Endlessly witty, visually rapturous, and sweetly romantic, Shakespeare in Love is a delightful romantic comedy that succeeds on nearly every level.
name: Shakespeare_in_Love

title: Still Alice
tomatoConsensus: Elevated by a gripping performance from Julianne Moore, Still Alice is a heartfelt drama that honors its delicate themes with bravery and sensitivity.
name: Still_Alice

title: The Babadook
tomatoConsensus: The Babadook relies on real horror rather than cheap jump scares -- and boasts a heartfelt, genuinely moving story to boot.
name: The_Babadook

title: The Birdcage
awards: Nominated for 1 Oscar. Another 6 wins & 17 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Mike Nichols wrangles agreeably amusing performances from Robin Williams and Nathan Lane in this fun, if not quite essential, remake of the French comedy La Cage aux Folles.
name: The_Birdcage

title: The Blair Witch Project
tomatoConsensus: Full of creepy campfire scares, mock-doc The Blair Witch Project keeps audiences in the dark about its titular villain -- thus proving that imagination can be as scary as anything onscreen.
name: The_Blair_Witch_Project

title: The Book of Life
awards: Nominated for 1 Golden Globe. Another 1 win & 22 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: The Book of Life's gorgeous animation is a treat, but it's a pity that its story lacks the same level of craft and detail that its thrilling visuals provide.
name: The_Book_of_Life

title: The Bourne Legacy
tomatoConsensus: It isn't quite as compelling as the earlier trilogy, but The Bourne Legacy proves the franchise has stories left to tell -- and benefits from Jeremy Renner's magnetic work in the starring role.
name: The_Bourne_Legacy

title: The Cobbler
tomatoConsensus: The Cobbler represents a slight step up from Adam Sandler's recent comedies, but while its cloying sentiment proves a more palatable substitute for his usual crass humor, it still isn't terribly compelling.
name: The_Cobbler

title: The Dark Knight
tomatoConsensus: Dark, complex and unforgettable, The Dark Knight succeeds not just as an entertaining comic book film, but as a richly thrilling crime saga.
name: The_Dark_Knight

title: The Fault in Our Stars
tomatoConsensus: Wise, funny, and heartbreaking without resorting to exploitation, The Fault In Our Stars does right by its bestselling source material.
name: The_Fault_in_Our_Stars

title: The Great Gatsby
tomatoConsensus: While certainly ambitious -- and every bit as visually dazzling as one might expect -- Baz Luhrmann's The Great Gatsby emphasizes visual splendor at the expense of its source material's vibrant heart.
name: The_Great_Gatsby

title: The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug
awards: Nominated for 3 Oscars. Another 15 wins & 74 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: While still slightly hamstrung by 'middle chapter' narrative problems and its formidable length, The Desolation of Smaug represents a more confident, exciting second chapter for the Hobbit series.
name: The_Hobbit__The_Desolation_of_Smaug

title: The Hunger Games
awards: Nominated for 1 Golden Globe. Another 32 wins & 40 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Thrilling and superbly acted, The Hunger Games captures the dramatic violence, raw emotion, and ambitious scope of its source novel.
name: The_Hunger_Games

title: The Hunger Games: Catching Fire
awards: Nominated for 1 Golden Globe. Another 24 wins & 52 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Smart, smoothly directed, and enriched with a deeper exploration of the franchise's thought-provoking themes, Catching Fire proves a thoroughly compelling second installment in the Hunger Games series.
name: The_Hunger_Games__Catching_Fire

title: The Imitation Game
tomatoConsensus: With an outstanding starring performance from Benedict Cumberbatch illuminating its fact-based story, The Imitation Game serves as an eminently well-made entry in the 'prestige biopic' genre.
name: The_Imitation_Game

title: The Judge
awards: Nominated for 1 Oscar. Another 4 wins & 6 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Solidly cast and beautifully filmed but thoroughly cliched, The Judge seems destined to preside over a large jurisdiction of the basic cable afternoon-viewing circuit.
name: The_Judge

title: The Last Days on Mars
tomatoConsensus: Neither intelligent enough to work as thought-provoking sci-fi nor trashy enough to provide B-movie thrills, The Last Days on Mars proves as cinematically barren as the titular planet.
name: The_Last_Days_on_Mars

title: The Lizzie McGuire Movie
tomatoConsensus: Harmless piece of fluff that ought to satisfy fans of the TV show.
name: The_Lizzie_McGuire_Movie

title: The Matrix
tomatoConsensus: Thanks to the Wachowskis' imaginative vision, The Matrix is a smartly crafted combination of spectacular action and groundbreaking special effects.
name: The_Matrix

title: The Maze Runner
tomatoConsensus: With strong acting, a solid premise, and a refreshingly dark approach to its dystopian setting, The Maze Runner stands out from the crowded field of YA sci-fi adventures.
name: The_Maze_Runner

title: The Normal Heart
awards: Won 1 Golden Globe. Another 20 wins & 48 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Thanks to Emmy-worthy performances from a reputable cast, The Normal Heart is not only a powerful, heartbreaking drama, but also a vital document of events leading up to and through the early AIDS crisis.
name: The_Normal_Heart

title: The Parent Trap
tomatoConsensus: Writer-director Nancy Meyers takes the winning formula of the 1961 original and gives it an amiable modern spin, while young star Lindsay Lohan shines in her breakout role.
name: The_Parent_Trap

title: The Reader
tomatoConsensus: Despite Kate Winslet's superb portrayal, The Reader suggests an emotionally distant, Oscar-baiting historical drama.
name: The_Reader

title: The Theory of Everything
tomatoConsensus: Part biopic, part love story, The Theory of Everything rises on James Marsh's polished direction and the strength of its two leads.
name: The_Theory_of_Everything

title: This Is Where I Leave You
tomatoConsensus: This Is Where I Leave You has its moments, but given the amount of talent assembled onscreen, the rather pedestrian results can't help but feel like a letdown.
name: This_Is_Where_I_Leave_You

title: Total Recall
awards: Nominated for 2 Oscars. Another 7 wins & 13 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Under Paul Verhoeven's frenetic direction, Total Recall is a fast-paced rush of violence, gore, and humor that never slacks.
name: Total_Recall

title: Transformers: Age of Extinction
tomatoConsensus: With the fourth installment in Michael Bay's blockbuster Transformers franchise, nothing is in disguise: Fans of loud, effects-driven action will find satisfaction, and all others need not apply.
name: Transformers__Age_of_Extinction

title: V for Vendetta
tomatoConsensus: Visually stunning and thought-provoking, V For Vendetta's political pronouncements may rile some, but its story and impressive set pieces will nevertheless entertain.
name: V_for_Vendetta

title: Welcome to Me
tomatoConsensus: A transfixing central performance by Kristen Wiig performance holds Welcome to Me together and compensates for its uneven stretches.
name: Welcome_to_Me

title: Wild Tales
awards: Nominated for 1 Oscar. Another 23 wins & 36 nominations.
tomatoConsensus: Wickedly hilarious and delightfully deranged, Wild Tales is a subversive satire that doubles as a uniformly entertaining anthology film.
name: Wild_Tales

title: Words and Pictures
tomatoConsensus: While both talented performers in their own right, Juliette Binoche and Clive Owen are decidedly mismatched in Words and Pictures, and they aren't done many favors by the movie's awkwardly constructed screenplay.
name: Words_and_Pictures
